Adding a new icons
==================

Use the fantastic script get-icon.sh! Suppose you want to add a new icon for
the "open" action. You find that Nuovo theme has a nice button under stock,
called gtk-open.svg. You call the script as follows:

$ sh get-icon.sh open Nuovo stock/gtk-open.svg

The script generates the PNG and updates both style.css and this very file
(listing below).

Source and Licensing
====================

Icons are taken from GNOME/Gtk+ themes on Debian systems. Normally they are
converted from SVG to PNG using rsvg (from package librsvg2-bin).

